openresty

This module can be used to install openresty from source on Linux systems (CentOs/Amazn Linux/Redhat).
This module compiles openresty from source with the following modules:
HTTP SSL - Lua JIT - PCRE and PCRE JIT

Usage :- 
Clone the module to your modulepath on the puppet server (Usually /etc/puppet/modules directory) and include the class "openresty" in your module files.
To test the module , you may use the below from the modules directory :-

sudo puppet apply openresty/tests/init.pp
 
Prerequisites :-
Your machine should be connected to the internet with the yum/apt package repo reachable.
